The pattern has a name

What you're describing is called "feature interaction complexity" and it grows non-linearly.

Think about it this way:

    With 10 features in the system, there are roughly 45 possible feature interactions to consider
    With 50 features, that's over 1,200 possible interactions
    With 100 features, it's nearly 5,000

No PO, no developer, no architect can hold all of that in their head. This is why the process has to do the work that human memory cannot.

