What Devin will struggle with

Be aware of these gaps so you validate for them:

    Intent behind rules — Devin can document what the rule is but not why it exists. The "why" often matters for future teams. You need to add that manually.
    Rules enforced in the UI — if some validation only happens in Angular/frontend code, Devin may miss it if scoped to the backend
    Rules that are missing — Devin can only document what's there. It can't tell you that the category-to-Other transition should clear associations but doesn't. That gap requires human knowledge.
    Implicit rules in DB constraints — if business logic is enforced via Oracle constraints or triggers rather than Java code, make sure Devin's scope includes the schema

